Generally, each plaque has its origin in the viral infection of a single cell. The reduction of virus titer shows directly the efficiency of an siRNA as the virus spread is prevented.
Seed 1.5–2.5  ×  105 HeLa cells per well in a volume of 500 μl of medium without antibiotics in a 24 well plate.Incubate overnight at 37°C and 5% CO2.Dilute siRNA (designed antiviral siRNA or a negative control siRNA with no matches either to the viral or target organism genome) in Opti-MEM or serum-free medium to a volume of 50 μl. The molar concentrations are related to the final volume of 600 μl.Prepare as many siRNA transfected wells as needed to titrate the different virus dilutions. Include positive control wells which remain untransfected, but will be infected with different virus dilutions.Premix 2 μl of Lipofectamine 2000 transfection reagent with 48 μl Opti-MEM.Incubated for 5 min at room temperature.Combine Lipofectamine and siRNA and incubate for at least 20 min.Add the final mix (100 μl per well) to the cells.Incubate for at least 4 h at 37°C and 5% CO2 (see Note 17).Cells should be close to 100% confluent before overlaying the infected cell monolayer.Prepare serial 1:10 dilutions of the virus stock in refrigerator-cold serum-free medium without antibiotics (see Note 19). In general, an appropriate range of dilutions is 10−4 to 10−7 (depending on the titer of virus stock).Incubate at 37°C for 5 min before adding to the cells. Virus dilutions can be stored at 4°C for several minutes, if necessary.Add 250 μl per well of the diluted virus suspension. Include negative control wells that remain uninfected. To this end, use serum-free medium without antibiotics and handle these cells identically to infected cells.Incubate for 30 min at 37°C and 5% CO2 (see Note 20).Remove the virus suspension by gentle aspiration.Add 4 ml FCS to 20 ml Eagle-MEM and prewarm to 41.5°C.Melt 0.28 g of Difco Agar Noble in 16 ml H2O. Cool to 40–45°C and add the prewarmed Eagle-MEM to the Agar Noble solution.Incubate for 15 min at 41.5°C. This makes a 0.7% Agar Noble solution (Eagle Overlay) which is used to overlay the infected cell monolayer.Add 500 μl per well of Eagle Overlay and leave the plates for 5 min at room temperature. Take care not to dislodge any cells.Incubate at 37°C and 5% CO2. Plaques should be visible within around 3 days depending on the virus.Add 500 μl of neutral red solution to each of the wells and incubate for 3–4 h at 37°C and 5% CO2 (see Note 21).Remove the stain by gentle aspiration.Invert the plate and count the plaques in each well.Calculate the viral titer of each well.
